## React Cheat Sheet

### Component (Functional)
```jsx
function Button({ text, onClick, disabled = false }) {
  return (
    <button onClick={onClick} disabled={disabled}
      className="btn">
      {text}
    </button>
  );
}
```

### State — useState
```jsx
const [count, setCount] = useState(0);
setCount(count + 1);        // update
setCount(prev => prev + 1); // safer with closures
```

### Side Effects — useEffect
```jsx
// Runs after every render
useEffect(() => { ... });
// Runs once on mount
useEffect(() => { ... }, []);
// Runs when userId changes
useEffect(() => { fetchUser(userId); }, [userId]);
// Cleanup (subscription, timer, event listener)
useEffect(() => {
  const id = setInterval(tick, 1000);
  return () => clearInterval(id); // cleanup
}, []);
```

### Context — shared state
```jsx
const ThemeContext = createContext('light');
// Provider
<ThemeContext.Provider value="dark">
  <App />
</ThemeContext.Provider>
// Consumer
const theme = useContext(ThemeContext);
```

### Common Patterns
- **Conditional render**: `{isLoggedIn && <Dashboard />}`
- **List render**: `{items.map(i => <Item key={i.id} {...i} />)}`
- **Lifting state**: Move state to nearest common ancestor
- **Controlled input**: `<input value={val} onChange={e => setVal(e.target.value)} />`
